{# ============================================================================
   Template:   routing.j2
   Phase:      routing — Route Decision Gate
   Purpose:    Evaluate all post-phase audit results, issue severity, and
               convergence state to decide the NEXT phase target.
               This template is NOT sent to Aider — it generates a structured
               routing analysis document consumed by routing.py internally.
               However, in SPECIAL cases where routing is ambiguous (e.g.,
               P1 that could be design-level OR implementation-level), this
               template can be rendered into an Aider prompt to ask Aider to
               help classify the issue severity and recommend a route target.
   Variables:
     {{ goal }}                  — string,  required.  User's original request.
     {{ current_phase }}         — string,  required.  The phase we are routing FROM.
     {{ cycle }}                 — integer, required.  Current cycle number.
     {{ convergence_counter }}   — integer, required.  Current convergence count.
     {{ convergence_rounds }}    — integer, required.  Threshold for termination.
     {{ max_cycles }}            — integer, required.  Hard stop limit.
     {{ active_issues }}         — dict,    required.  {"p0": [...], "p1": [...], "p2": [...]}.
     {{ resolved_issues }}       — dict,    required.  {"p0": N, "p1": N, "p2": N}.
     {{ tasks }}                 — dict,    required.  {"total": N, "by_status": {...}}.
     {{ route_repeat_max }}      — integer, required.  Threshold for repeat-detection pause.
     {{ routing_history }}       — list,    required.  Prior routing decisions.
     {{ routing_repeat_tracker }}— dict,    required.  Repeat-count tracker.
     {{ phase_contracts }}       — dict,    required.  Contracts for all phases.
     {{ all_audit_results }}     — list,    required.  Post-call audit results from the
                                                      most recent phase execution.
     {{ verification_pass_count }}— integer, required.  Count of consecutive verification passes.
     {{ mode }}                  — string,  required.  Trust level (safe/auto/unsafe/interactive).
   Output:  routing decision (written to state.json by routing.py, not Aider)
   ============================================================================ #}

