## 4. ROUTING DECISION TREE

The routing algorithm (`routing.py`) evaluates conditions in this exact order.
The FIRST matching condition wins.

### Priority 1 — P0 Detected
{% raw %}
**Condition:** `any(active_issues.p0)`
**Target:** `part_1_1` (back to requirements)
**Action:** Reset `part1_round = 0`, `cycle += 1`
**Rationale:** Directional error — the foundation is wrong.  Must re-design.

### Priority 2 — Design-level P1 Detected
**Condition:** `any(active_issues.p1) AND issue.is_design_level == true`
**Target:** `part_1_3` (back to solution design)
**Action:** `cycle += 1`
**Rationale:** Core defect caused by design flaw.  Re-design the affected
component, not just patch code.

### Priority 3 — Implementation-level P1 Detected
**Condition:** `any(active_issues.p1) AND issue.is_design_level == false`
**Target:** `part_2_2` with `repair_context` populated
**Action:** `cycle += 1`
**Rationale:** Core defect in implementation.  Targeted repair, not full redo.

### Priority 4 — P2 Detected
**Condition:** `any(active_issues.p2)`
**Target:** `part_2_2` with `repair_context` populated
**Action:** `cycle += 1`
**Rationale:** Quality issues — patch in implementation phase.

### Priority 5 — All Clear + Convergence Met
**Condition:** `NO active issues AND convergence_counter >= convergence_rounds`
**Target:** `complete` — termination
**Action:** Set `termination.status = "complete"`
**Rationale:** Problem list is empty and we have sustained convergence.

### Priority 6 — All Clear + Convergence Not Met + Verification Needed
**Condition:** `NO active issues AND convergence_counter < convergence_rounds AND verification_pass_count < convergence_rounds`
**Target:** `part_2_8` (re-verification)
**Action:** `verification_pass_count += 1`
**Rationale:** Looks good but need sustained stability proof.

### Priority 7 — All Clear + Convergence Not Met + Equivalent Convergence
**Condition:** `NO active issues AND convergence_counter < convergence_rounds AND verification_pass_count >= convergence_rounds`
**Target:** `complete` — equivalent convergence
**Action:** Set `termination.status = "complete"`
**Rationale:** Continuous re-verification with zero new findings equals convergence.

### Priority 8 — Cycle Limit Reached
**Condition:** `cycle >= max_cycles`
**Target:** `complete` — forced termination
**Action:** Set `termination.status = "complete"`, `exit_reason = "max_cycles"`
**Rationale:** Hard stop to prevent infinite loops.

### Priority 9 — Route Repeat Detected
**Condition:** `routing_repeat_tracker[route_key] >= route_repeat_max`
**Target:** `paused` — request user intervention
**Action:** Set `phase = "paused"`, `termination.status = "paused"`
**Rationale:** The same route loop has repeated too many times; human judgment needed.

### Priority 10 — No Issues, Ongoing Work
**Condition:** `NO active issues AND tasks.by_status.in_progress > 0`
**Target:** `part_2_2` (continue implementation)
**Action:** No cycle increment
**Rationale:** Work is still in progress but no quality issues yet.
{% endraw %}

